article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 76, Texas State 59
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Paez scored 15 points as Stephen F. Austin beat Texas State 76-59 on Wednesday night. Stephen F. Austin (11-9, 5-4 Southland Conference) trailed early before going on a 22-0 run in the first half, holding Texas State (11-10, 5-5) scoreless for more than 11 minutes during that stretch. Josh Porter added 12 points and Hank Rivers had 11 rebounds for the Lumberjacks. Josh Naylor scored 19 points and Markee White had 14 for Texas State. Texas State recovered from shooting 26 percent in the first half to shoot 60 percent in the second. But the Lumberjacks dominated the Bobcats on the boards, outrebounding Texas State 40-23.
